even as your father suffers...?

251
00:26:35,439 --> 00:26:37,672
Aw now that just ain't nice.

252
00:26:37,672 --> 00:26:39,939
You don't have
to listen to that shit.

253
00:26:39,939 --> 00:26:43,772
(taunting)
And you have such
a long long way to go...

254
00:26:43,772 --> 00:26:47,572
to save your
poor tortured father.

255
00:26:47,572 --> 00:26:49,905
I've almost revived
his rotten bones.

256
00:26:49,905 --> 00:26:52,439
Oh, he <i>will</i> live again...

257
00:26:52,439 --> 00:26:56,605
...to feel <i>pain</i>, to <i>suffer</i>.

258
00:26:56,605 --> 00:26:57,605
(mocking) And you
don't even have

259
00:26:57,605 --> 00:27:00,705
the #2 headband yet.

260
00:27:00,705 --> 00:27:02,539
So I have a few more days,

261
00:27:02,539 --> 00:27:04,772
or maybe even weeks,

262
00:27:04,772 --> 00:27:07,572
to enjoy your father's
pain before you

263
00:27:07,572 --> 00:27:11,772
even have the right
to challenge me...

264
00:27:20,439 --> 00:27:24,939
(slowly with anger)
Watch... your damn... mouth.

265
00:27:28,639 --> 00:27:32,272
Cause I'm comin' for my dad.

266
00:27:53,339 --> 00:27:55,772
Then we comin' to get you bitch!

267
00:27:55,772 --> 00:28:01,872
Finally you are
awake my hated love.

268
00:28:01,872 --> 00:28:05,672
Now the fun begins...

269
00:28:05,672 --> 00:28:09,905
Whoa. She don't know
who she's fuckin' with.

270
00:28:21,505 --> 00:28:22,872
Jinno...

271
00:28:23,772 --> 00:28:26,305
At last, he has begun to move...

272
00:28:26,305 --> 00:28:28,572
All is proceeding as planned.

273
00:28:28,572 --> 00:28:31,405
We will have our revenge.

274
00:28:31,405 --> 00:28:33,605
But, to succeed,
you and I, my love,

275
00:28:33,605 --> 00:28:37,839
must walk the path of demons.

276
00:28:37,839 --> 00:28:42,939
I am truly sorry but it is the
only way to make him feel the

277
00:28:42,939 --> 00:28:47,505
eternal sadness
that we have felt,

278
00:28:47,505 --> 00:28:52,872
to make him suffer
as we have suffered.

279
00:28:52,872 --> 00:28:55,472
So please...

280
00:28:55,472 --> 00:28:57,639
...forgive me.

281
00:28:57,639 --> 00:29:04,805
Just remember that there
was no alternative.

282
00:29:04,805 --> 00:29:07,239
I will always love you...

283
00:29:08,805 --> 00:29:10,772
My beloved brother.

284
00:29:33,039 --> 00:29:34,939
Your luck sucks, man.

285
00:29:34,939 --> 00:29:36,872
Everybody knows this is the

286
00:29:36,872 --> 00:29:39,539
first day of the yearly
parade around here.

287
00:29:39,539 --> 00:29:40,539
You ain't gonna get no info

288
00:29:40,539 --> 00:29:44,472
from these party people
about that #2 headband.

289
00:29:44,472 --> 00:29:45,972
His name was Shichogoro right?

290
00:29:45,972 --> 00:29:49,472
You even got any idea
what he look like? I don't!

291
00:29:49,472 --> 00:29:52,772
How we even know that's
his real damn name?!?

292
00:30:01,972 --> 00:30:06,439
The point I am trying to make
is that this is all a bad idea!

293
00:30:13,639 --> 00:30:17,772
Help! Help! Help!

294
00:30:17,772 --> 00:30:19,339
What the?

295
00:30:19,572 --> 00:30:20,972
Out of my way!

296
00:30:20,972 --> 00:30:23,272
A kidnappin' in broad daylight?

297
00:30:23,272 --> 00:30:25,372
That's a damn shame.

298
00:30:26,305 --> 00:30:30,572
(suddenly realizes)
Ah shit... Afro Samurai?

299
00:30:32,772 --> 00:30:34,572
‐‐Out of my way!
‐‐Whoa! Damn!

300
00:30:34,572 --> 00:30:37,472
I said move
you son of a bitch!!!

301
00:30:37,472 --> 00:30:41,772
Gun! Afro! Gun! Heater!
Rosco! Gat! Duck!

302
00:30:50,272 --> 00:30:51,639
Gahhh!!!!

303
00:31:02,005 --> 00:31:04,239
Waa! Waa!

304
00:31:09,605 --> 00:31:11,239
(Off‐screen) Kotaro!

305
00:31:17,939 --> 00:31:20,939
(crying) Oh Daddy!!

306
00:31:25,939 --> 00:31:30,305
Kotaro.
I told you to stay close.

307
00:31:30,305 --> 00:31:31,739
I'm sorry...

308
00:31:35,905 --> 00:31:38,872
You. You have my thanks.

309
00:31:38,872 --> 00:31:41,605
(to the dead body) This
coward kidnapped my boy to...

310
00:31:43,339 --> 00:31:44,872
(changes his mind) Forget it.

311
00:31:48,839 --> 00:31:50,672
Let me buy you a drink...
(points with his thumb).

312
00:31:50,672 --> 00:31:52,705
...I know a spot nearby.

313
00:31:59,739 --> 00:32:02,972
Uh‐oh. I think I lost
a Ninja boot! Wait!

314
00:32:02,972 --> 00:32:06,439
I'm drowning! Hey! Afro!

315
00:32:06,439 --> 00:32:08,472
Don't leave a brotha!

316
00:33:22,772 --> 00:33:24,905
I'm home old man!

317
00:33:26,639 --> 00:33:29,772
Hey hey! You brought
a friend today?

318
00:33:29,772 --> 00:33:33,305
This man saved Kotaro'S life.

319
00:33:33,305 --> 00:33:34,639
So maybe he's strong enough

320
00:33:34,639 --> 00:33:37,372
not to die from
your stew ole man.

321
00:33:38,672 --> 00:33:40,939
Watch your mouth when
you talk about my oden

322
00:33:40,939 --> 00:33:45,539
Shichogoro, or you might
find a hot pepper in your bowl.

323
00:33:45,539 --> 00:33:47,905
You call this crap oden? Ha!

324
00:33:47,905 --> 00:33:50,472
More like chunky rat poison!

325
00:33:50,472 --> 00:33:52,339
Anyway, give me and the kid two

326
00:33:52,339 --> 00:33:56,705
of the usual and throw in
a couple cups of sake. Hot.

327
00:33:56,705 --> 00:33:58,505
Coming right up!

328
00:33:58,505 --> 00:34:00,639
(Happily)
Chunky rat poison!

329
00:34:01,639 --> 00:34:05,739
Just for you,
you little street rat!

330
00:34:07,372 --> 00:34:09,339
You're the street rat!

331
00:34:17,972 --> 00:34:22,305
Hey I'm back! Found my shoe too!

332
00:34:22,305 --> 00:34:25,639
Oh, ya getting' your
grub on? Oh, ewwww...

333
00:34:25,639 --> 00:34:27,372
Somethin' smells funky!

334
00:34:28,339 --> 00:34:30,505
Oh shit! That's the dude!?!

335
00:34:32,539 --> 00:34:34,439
(smiling at Afro)
Whaddya have, partner?

336
00:34:36,039 --> 00:34:37,472
Sukiyaki.

337
00:34:37,472 --> 00:34:39,005
Double that!

338
00:35:00,572 --> 00:35:02,305
Here's to you.

339
00:35:02,972 --> 00:35:05,605
Oh, not a drinker, eh?

340
00:35:05,605 --> 00:35:08,339
Don't know what you're missin'!

341
00:35:08,339 --> 00:35:09,872
Lemonade, then?

342
00:35:13,005 --> 00:35:15,605
Kidding. Kidding.

343
00:35:15,605 --> 00:35:18,672
(takes the bottle for himself.)
Forget it. I'll drink both.

344
00:35:24,005 --> 00:35:27,305
You aren't here for
the festival, are you..?

345
00:35:27,305 --> 00:35:30,005
Me neither.
Just passing through.

346
00:35:32,605 --> 00:35:35,405
But, I guess
we overstayed a bit.

347
00:35:37,339 --> 00:35:39,839
We had our chuckles
at the festival.

348
00:35:39,839 --> 00:35:42,605
But, it's best we move on.

349
00:35:47,805 --> 00:35:50,705
Ya know, it sucks
that you gotta kill this dude.

350
00:35:50,705 --> 00:35:54,372
I gotta say, he ain't
so bad! Kinda cool...

351
00:36:09,405 --> 00:36:13,005
It's always lonely
after the festival.

352
00:36:13,939 --> 00:36:15,672
At least this
is the last time I'll

353
00:36:15,672 --> 00:36:18,005
have to eat
your lousy rat poison!

354
00:36:20,339 --> 00:36:22,605
You'll be sorry.
I make the best stew

355
00:36:22,605 --> 00:36:24,439
for miles around.
When you come back‐‐

356
00:36:24,439 --> 00:36:27,305
remind me to charge you double.

357
00:36:27,305 --> 00:36:31,705
Jeeeeesus! This is the best?

358
00:36:31,705 --> 00:36:35,339
Afro, maybe you oughta kill
this motha fucka too for lying.

359
00:36:35,339 --> 00:36:37,272
This stew sucks!

360
00:36:39,572 --> 00:36:43,705
Lemonade. Please. Help yourself.

361
00:36:52,972 --> 00:36:54,639
That guy earlier...

362
00:36:54,639 --> 00:36:56,672
That man you cut down.

363
00:36:56,672 --> 00:36:59,372
You want to know why
he tried to kidnap Kotaro?

364
00:36:59,372 --> 00:37:00,372
Hell, no.

365
00:37:00,372 --> 00:37:01,405
Do you want to know why anyone

366
00:37:01,405 --> 00:37:04,472
bothers with a street kid
and a drunk like me?

367
00:37:04,472 --> 00:37:05,339
Hell, no.

368
00:37:05,339 --> 00:37:06,605
(Trying to interrupt)
Shichogoro...

369
00:37:06,605 --> 00:37:08,639
It's OK, ole man.

370
00:37:08,639 --> 00:37:10,372
Okay, tell us.

371
00:37:16,872 --> 00:37:19,905
I got something
everybody wants...

372
00:37:45,005 --> 00:37:46,939
One minute he's
stuffing his face,

373
00:37:46,939 --> 00:37:48,972
the next he's passed out.

374
00:37:48,972 --> 00:37:51,939
He ain't even mine.
He's an orphan‐‐

375
00:37:51,939 --> 00:37:55,439
the son of a pal who
got himself murdered.

376
00:37:55,439 --> 00:37:59,872
I promised to watch him if he
ever got in trouble or killed.

377
00:37:59,872 --> 00:38:03,739
Me and that old bastard
were like brothers.

378
00:38:03,739 --> 00:38:07,839
He wasn't the brightest,
but he was a good man.

379
00:38:07,839 --> 00:38:11,305
He died when this kid was a pup.

380
00:38:11,305 --> 00:38:15,005
I heard the man who killed
him had a weird look.

381
00:38:15,005 --> 00:38:17,839
An Afro hairdo with
a greenish tint

382
00:38:17,839 --> 00:38:19,639
if you look real close.

383
00:38:21,605 --> 00:38:25,772
Now you listen to
me and you listen good.

384
00:38:25,772 --> 00:38:27,405
In this world,

385
00:38:27,405 --> 00:38:31,005
there are bonds
deeper than blood...

386
00:38:32,505 --> 00:38:35,272
(Suddenly waking‐up)
Huh? Wha?

387
00:38:35,272 --> 00:38:37,339
My pal, that dumb
son‐of‐a‐bitch,

388
00:38:37,339 --> 00:38:38,939
he was like so
many fools who went

389
00:38:38,939 --> 00:38:40,905
after those headbands of legend.

390
00:38:40,905 --> 00:38:44,405
All he wound‐up
was dead. (Pause)

391
00:38:44,405 --> 00:38:47,005
Know what he said to me
when I found him dying?

392
00:38:49,039 --> 00:38:53,939
"No more," he whispered.

393
00:38:53,939 --> 00:38:59,305
So, I got that #2 headband
myself and I hid it.

394
00:38:59,305 --> 00:39:02,305
Been on the run ever since.

395
00:39:12,772 --> 00:39:14,805
But now you've come...

396
00:39:29,639 --> 00:39:31,639
(Looking at Afro)
...and now we're even.

397
00:39:33,005 --> 00:39:36,805
So, let's get this over with.

398
00:39:39,005 --> 00:39:42,505
(Enthusiastically)
Oh damn! It's ON now!

399
00:39:42,505 --> 00:39:46,005
No more Mr. Nice Afro!

400
00:39:46,005 --> 00:39:47,739
Shichogoro...!

401
00:39:48,939 --> 00:39:51,772
(smiles) Keep that
poison hot ole man.

402
00:39:51,772 --> 00:39:53,805
I'll be back in a flash.

403
00:39:59,539 --> 00:40:01,439
Hm...

404
00:40:33,235 --> 00:40:36,935
(chuckle)
I thought if Kotaro
and me just kept movin...

405
00:40:36,935 --> 00:40:38,202
...maybe folks
would forget about

406
00:40:38,202 --> 00:40:39,835
it all and I could
honor my pal's

407
00:40:39,835 --> 00:40:42,935
wish of peace for his son.

408
00:40:43,835 --> 00:40:49,535
But I guess there ain't
no hidin' from fate. Dammit.

409
00:40:49,535 --> 00:40:54,635
All these damn headbands do is
make dead buddies and orphans.

410
00:40:54,635 --> 00:40:56,769
You hear me Afro?

411
00:40:56,769 --> 00:41:00,235
Dead bodies and orphans!

412
00:41:00,235 --> 00:41:04,935
So, I ain't givin you
the #2 headband.

413
00:41:04,935 --> 00:41:08,102
You'll have to
kill me to get it.

414
00:41:08,102 --> 00:41:09,602
Not because I'm playin' by

415
00:41:09,602 --> 00:41:11,135
the headband rules,
and not because

416
00:41:11,135 --> 00:41:14,102
I'm out to save
the world neither!

417
00:41:17,869 --> 00:41:21,669
Yo Afro! What's‐up
with the formal stance?

418
00:41:21,669 --> 00:41:24,535
He cool and all,
but he ain't your pal!

419
00:41:24,535 --> 00:41:26,469
Just dent this fool!

420
00:41:32,602 --> 00:41:36,035
It's because I keep my promises.

421
00:42:44,935 --> 00:42:48,802
Don't think I don't know
you Afro Samurai.

422
00:42:48,802 --> 00:42:51,935
I saw what you
did on the boardwalk.

423
00:42:51,935 --> 00:42:55,635
Killing a man without
a moment of hesitation‐‐

424
00:42:55,635 --> 00:43:00,169
like he was nothin'
but a fly on your face.

425
00:43:00,169 --> 00:43:04,569
Maybe it's time
someone swatted you.

426
00:43:04,569 --> 00:43:07,702
Maybe I feel like
I'm the guy to do it.

427
00:43:07,702 --> 00:43:09,669
You gonna let
him talk all that trash?

428
00:43:09,669 --> 00:43:12,135
Slice him and dice him, Afro!

429
00:43:18,069 --> 00:43:22,235
Sayonara Afro Samurai.

430
00:43:22,235 --> 00:43:23,869
Now that's just wack.

431
00:43:23,869 --> 00:43:25,802
You gonna die creep!

432
00:43:37,802 --> 00:43:39,169
(painful grunt)
Guh!!!

433
00:44:12,902 --> 00:44:15,602
Shit! This guy's slick!

434
00:44:15,602 --> 00:44:19,769
I'm impressed! He just
might kill your ass!

435
00:44:47,902 --> 00:44:50,069
Aww man, you runnin?

436
00:44:50,069 --> 00:44:51,702
You makin' us look bad dude!

437
00:44:51,702 --> 00:44:53,602
Where you going?

438
00:45:05,835 --> 00:45:07,902
Ahhh, I knew you
was bein' devious!

439
00:45:07,902 --> 00:45:09,735
We ain't never run
from nobody,

440
00:45:09,735 --> 00:45:12,569
and we ain't about to
pick today to start running!

441
00:45:12,569 --> 00:45:14,269
Hey man! Keep on swingin'!

442
00:45:14,269 --> 00:45:16,202
Whilst I get my groove on!

443
00:45:16,202 --> 00:45:20,635
Let's paaaarrrttaaayyyy!

444
00:45:39,802 --> 00:45:43,502
Awwwwww shit!
Now we partyin' like rockstars!

445
00:45:43,502 --> 00:45:46,002
Light show! Light show!

446
00:45:46,002 --> 00:45:48,469
(pumping his voice to the beat)
Mmm... mmm!

447
00:46:13,969 --> 00:46:16,702
Bring it baby.

448
00:46:16,702 --> 00:46:19,835
Yeah, boom boom.

449
00:46:50,002 --> 00:46:51,269
Yeah yeah, whuddup yo!

450
00:46:51,269 --> 00:46:53,202
We're gonna get this party
crackin' right now!

451
00:46:53,202 --> 00:46:54,735
Now on center stage:

452
00:46:54,735 --> 00:46:56,902
we got the man with
the No.2 headband!

453
00:46:56,902 --> 00:46:58,535
Don't stop, get it, get it!

454
00:46:58,535 --> 00:47:01,069
Buzza buzza boom! Buzza boom!

455
00:47:27,002 --> 00:47:29,235
(Dropping his light sticks)
Hey! Where'd they come from?

456
00:47:34,869 --> 00:47:38,169
Urgh! This is only half‐cooked.

457
00:47:38,169 --> 00:47:39,669
You expect me to eat this?

458
00:47:39,669 --> 00:47:41,202
I broke my teeth on this crap.

459
00:47:41,202 --> 00:47:42,535
This is disgusting.

460
00:47:42,535 --> 00:47:44,035
How do you even
stay in business?

461
00:47:44,035 --> 00:47:45,602
Come on, let's get out of here.

462
00:47:45,602 --> 00:47:48,569
This place should be shut down.

463
00:47:53,702 --> 00:47:55,069
Dad...?

464
00:48:01,235 --> 00:48:02,802
Kotaro?

465
00:48:20,602 --> 00:48:24,135
Aww man!
You've killed the music!

466
00:48:24,135 --> 00:48:27,702
Why you always got to
wreck the party!?!

467
00:48:31,269 --> 00:48:35,935
Well, that was an
unnecessary distraction.

468
00:48:35,935 --> 00:48:38,035
Still want to die?

469
00:48:44,502 --> 00:48:46,669
You want it that much?

470
00:48:46,669 --> 00:48:49,569
It's just a piece
of cloth you idiot.

471
00:48:53,635 --> 00:48:59,569
If you're feeling so lucky‐‐
come and get it.

472
00:49:29,102 --> 00:49:30,135
What the fu... (reaction)

473
00:49:30,135 --> 00:49:31,869
Shut up.

474
00:50:30,535 --> 00:50:32,735
Sumanai.
("sorry" in samurai dialect)

475
00:51:18,810 --> 00:51:22,689
Man you always got to
bust‐up the fun don't you.

476
00:51:22,689 --> 00:51:25,556
I was ravin' til the
break a dawn man!

477
00:51:25,556 --> 00:51:27,622
Light sticks and everything!

478
00:51:27,622 --> 00:51:29,422
Why'd you go and ruin it?

479
00:51:29,422 --> 00:51:31,156
I bet they even
cancel the damn thing

480
00:51:31,156 --> 00:51:33,456
next year and
its all your fault.

481
00:51:33,456 --> 00:51:36,656
And another thing...
you ain't all that,

482
00:51:36,656 --> 00:51:40,722
just cause you back
to being the #2 again!

483
00:51:40,722 --> 00:51:42,222
Don't you get it?

484
00:51:42,222 --> 00:51:45,089
We walkin' the demon path again!

485
00:51:45,089 --> 00:51:47,122
It ain't the right way!

486
00:51:52,156 --> 00:51:54,622
Ah well. Whatever.
So where we goin' next?

487
00:51:54,622 --> 00:51:57,289
How about getting
a little 'push push' first?

488
00:51:57,289 --> 00:51:58,756
Know what I'm sayin'?!?!

489
00:51:58,756 --> 00:52:00,656
Man we never party!

490
00:52:05,122 --> 00:52:08,056
Damn, now what's
fin to jump off?

491
00:52:15,356 --> 00:52:18,022
Whoa wait. Didn't they
already kick your ass?

492
00:52:18,022 --> 00:52:20,389
They coming after you again?

493
00:52:20,389 --> 00:52:24,289
Your blade stains
the world with blood.

494
00:52:24,289 --> 00:52:26,222
(sarcastic)
Oh you think!?

495
00:52:26,222 --> 00:52:29,589
You kill only for your
selfish petty reasons...

496
00:52:33,756 --> 00:52:35,722
Have you no heart?

497
00:52:50,089 --> 00:52:52,122
Uh... Urgh... Uh...

498
00:52:57,222 --> 00:52:58,522
(panicking)
This can't be real man.

499
00:52:58,522 --> 00:53:00,356
Who the hell are these people!

500
00:53:00,356 --> 00:53:02,256
This ain't possible!

